30002835@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:757@LMC@2019-06-14
30002836@@@@@@The infestation of the mynas is a prevalent thorn to our environment.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:758@LMC@2019-06-14
30002837@@@@@@Myna are known to encroach into territories of native bird species and in some cases, even attack humans for food.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:759@LMC@2019-06-14
30002838@@@@@@Therefore, their huge presence in the environment needs to be stamped.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:760@LMC@2019-06-14
30002839@@@@@@Washington Odongo Ochola mentioned that the proliferation of mynas is due to its superior ability to compete for food and nesting space [1].@@@@1@23@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:761@LMC@2019-06-14
30002840@@@@@@As such, to reduce their numbers, it is important to prevent myna from nesting and obtaining food.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:762@LMC@2019-06-14
30002841@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:763@LMC@2019-06-14
30002842@@@@@@To prevent infestations, several commercial methods are available.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:764@LMC@2019-06-14
30002843@@@@@@However, each have obvious limitations and could be improved on.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:765@LMC@2019-06-14
30002844@@@@@@One such method is the bird spikes, which are placed on canopies, preventing birds from nesting.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:766@LMC@2019-06-14
30002845@@@@@@However, they are aesthetically unpleasant and affect the natural beauty of the environment.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:767@LMC@2019-06-14
30002846@@@@@@Moreover, they are permanent fixtures and would lose their effectiveness when removed.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:768@LMC@2019-06-14
30002847@@@@@@Another method is the use of sonic repellers to chase away the mynas, but eventually the Myna would be conditioned to the sound and seeing no danger, would continue to plague the area [2].@@@@1@34@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:769@LMC@2019-06-14
30002848@@@@@@Solutions@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:770@LMC@2019-06-14
30002849@@@@@@The goal of this proposal is to integrate a sonic repeller to an existing misting system to deter mynas from finding available food source.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:771@LMC@2019-06-14
30002850@@@@@@This will put a strain on their population and ultimately eradicate the infestation.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:772@LMC@2019-06-14
30002851@@@@@@Echolalia is a small battery-powered device, no larger than a container size (15cm x 5cm).@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:773@LMC@2019-06-14
30002852@@@@@@To prevent disruption from birds, Users will be able to comfortably slot it around their premises, such as on trees or even on site.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:774@LMC@2019-06-14
30002853@@@@@@The sonic repeller will be programmed to mimic cries of distress of a myna, causing other myna to think that the surrounding area is dangerous and thus avoid it.@@@@1@29@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:775@LMC@2019-06-14
30002854@@@@@@The misting system which emits chemical that are irritable to mynas will help to further reinforce the perception of danger.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:776@LMC@2019-06-14
30002855@@@@@@Benefits@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:777@LMC@2019-06-14
30002856@@@@@@Echolalia brings about all the enhancements of pre-existing solutions on the market.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:778@LMC@2019-06-14
30002857@@@@@@It blends in with the environment, is highly compact and extremely rugged.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:779@LMC@2019-06-14
30002858@@@@@@It can be deployed even in Singapore’s tropical weather.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:780@LMC@2019-06-14
30002859@@@@@@The ‘Plant and Use’ convenience makes it user-friendly and easy access to the back panel of the device makes servicing extremely simple.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:99; ntucle-sid:781@LMC@2019-06-14
