30003161@@@@@@“Magic Print” Lock@@@@1@3@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:597@LMC@2019-06-14
30003162@@@@@@Background@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:598@LMC@2019-06-14
30003163@@@@@@In recent years, there have been many cases of missing valuables from the luggage reported by airline passengers.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:599@LMC@2019-06-14
30003164@@@@@@Although police have implemented measures to eradicate this problem, many similar cases are still reported every year.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:600@LMC@2019-06-14
30003165@@@@@@According to Spargo (2015), airline customers from Miami International Airport have reported $2.5 million in lost property from 2010 to 2014.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:601@LMC@2019-06-14
30003166@@@@@@It is found that most of the missing valuables were stolen from baggage handlers.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:602@LMC@2019-06-14
30003167@@@@@@In a news article by Squires(2013), 29 baggage handlers were arrested for stealing valuables from passengers’ suitcases.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:603@LMC@2019-06-14
30003168@@@@@@Problem@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:604@LMC@2019-06-14
30003169@@@@@@In order to deal with these theft cases, the police have installed hidden cameras to capture unscrupulous acts of the workers.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:605@LMC@2019-06-14
30003170@@@@@@Although those workers were subsequently arrested, it does not completely deter similar cases from occurring.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:606@LMC@2019-06-14
30003171@@@@@@This method is tedious as it requires constant monitoring of the screen so that the criminal could be arrested on the spot.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:607@LMC@2019-06-14
30003172@@@@@@Stolen valuables might not be recoverable and extra efforts are needed to trace them back.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:608@LMC@2019-06-14
30003173@@@@@@Therefore, there is a need to further investigate possible ways to completely eradicate this problem.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:609@LMC@2019-06-14
30003174@@@@@@Solution@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:610@LMC@2019-06-14
30003175@@@@@@The main goal of this project is to integrate “Magic Print” lock fitted with security alarm on the luggage to prevent theft.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:611@LMC@2019-06-14
30003176@@@@@@This additional new lock, which can save up to ten fingerprints and powered by two AAA batteries, will be used to improve on the current Travel Sentry Approved (TSA) key lock.@@@@1@31@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:612@LMC@2019-06-14
30003177@@@@@@“Magic Print” lock can only be unlocked using authorized fingerprints.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:613@LMC@2019-06-14
30003178@@@@@@If more than three attempts were made, the alarm would go off at a sound of 85 decibels.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:614@LMC@2019-06-14
30003179@@@@@@Any damage to the lock would also trigger the alarm.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:615@LMC@2019-06-14
30003180@@@@@@This alerts the police or people nearby.@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:616@LMC@2019-06-14
30003181@@@@@@Benefits@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:617@LMC@2019-06-14
30003182@@@@@@With this new implementation, users will definitely have a better sense of security when they checked in their luggage as it would be harder to unlock the luggage without alerting the police.@@@@1@32@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:618@LMC@2019-06-14
30003183@@@@@@Hence, this greatly reduces theft crime from occurring.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:619@LMC@2019-06-14
30003184@@@@@@Moreover, lesser police would be needed in the footage control station, allowing more police to be deployed elsewhere.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:620@LMC@2019-06-14
30003185@@@@@@Implementation@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:621@LMC@2019-06-14
30003186@@@@@@In order for the new implementation to be put in place, the following steps will be taken:@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:622@LMC@2019-06-14
30003187@@@@@@1@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:623@LMC@2019-06-14
30003188@@@@@@We will collaborate with a company which manufacture TSA lock to improve on their current lock.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:624@LMC@2019-06-14
30003189@@@@@@2@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:625@LMC@2019-06-14
30003190@@@@@@Astrol security Engineering PTE LTD, a high-tech company which specializes in security system, will help in designing and supplying both the fingerprint sensor and security alarm that are most suitable for the luggage.@@@@1@33@ntucle-docid:111; ntucle-sid:626@LMC@2019-06-14
