30003302@@@@@@STICKY POWER BANK@@@@1@3@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:763@LMC@2019-06-14
30003303@@@@@@BACKGROUND@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:764@LMC@2019-06-14
30003304@@@@@@Power bank has been increasingly popular in recent years.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:765@LMC@2019-06-14
30003305@@@@@@It is a portable extensive battery that is connected to the phone by USB cable, and is rechargeable.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:766@LMC@2019-06-14
30003306@@@@@@Its ability to give additional power to the phone can be very useful, especially for those who commute through the day.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:767@LMC@2019-06-14
30003307@@@@@@With various manufacturers of power bank providing different capacity of power available, users can choose to have one that suits their need.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:768@LMC@2019-06-14
30003308@@@@@@PROBLEM@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:769@LMC@2019-06-14
30003309@@@@@@However, many people often feel troubled with the size of the power bank they carry along.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:770@LMC@2019-06-14
30003310@@@@@@Many power banks offer great capacity, but they are also very bulky, not to mention the USB cable that often got tangled.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:771@LMC@2019-06-14
30003311@@@@@@People may want something that is more convenient to carry and does not take much space.@@@@1@16@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:772@LMC@2019-06-14
30003312@@@@@@Another problem is that many people claim power bank can cause damage to the phone battery as the current flowing into the phone is unstable.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:773@LMC@2019-06-14
30003313@@@@@@SOLUTION@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:774@LMC@2019-06-14
30003314@@@@@@We provide a solution to problems people have with their power banks.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:775@LMC@2019-06-14
30003315@@@@@@STICKY power bank is able to supply power to smartphones simply by sticking at the back of the phone.@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:776@LMC@2019-06-14
30003316@@@@@@Sticking is possible as there is magnetic force produced by the main component and our special case.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:777@LMC@2019-06-14
30003317@@@@@@Amazingly thin in size and made of lightweight materials, it offers an experience of using power bank like never before.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:778@LMC@2019-06-14
30003318@@@@@@BENEFITS@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:779@LMC@2019-06-14
30003319@@@@@@People do not need to carry hefty power banks anymore.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:780@LMC@2019-06-14
30003320@@@@@@With STICKY's streamline shape, people now can hold their phone and power bank like there is only "literally" their phone, which can be very convenient and flexible for people who always need a phone on their hand.@@@@1@37@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:781@LMC@2019-06-14
30003321@@@@@@Using magnetic technology, people also do not need to worry about untangling the USB cable or finding out the cable is suddenly pulled off.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:782@LMC@2019-06-14
30003322@@@@@@Our power bank is able to store 5000 mAh, and uses inductive charging method which can also ensure consumers that it produces more stable current.@@@@1@25@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:783@LMC@2019-06-14
30003323@@@@@@More stable compared to its competitors, it helps to keep the battery life longer.@@@@1@14@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:784@LMC@2019-06-14
30003324@@@@@@IMPLEMENTATION@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:785@LMC@2019-06-14
30003325@@@@@@The power bank sends alternating current to transmitter coil inside the main component, which is then transferred using electromagnetic field to the receiving coil inside phone battery (Curtis, 2015).@@@@1@29@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:786@LMC@2019-06-14
30003326@@@@@@The receiver circuit then converts the current into Direct Current (DC) to charge the battery.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:787@LMC@2019-06-14
30003327@@@@@@Magnetic field unfortunately affects magnetic sensors inside the phone, which disables GPS function, but users do not need to worry about it damaging the phone, as it is only a temporary effect (Newby, 2015).@@@@1@34@ntucle-docid:115; ntucle-sid:788@LMC@2019-06-14
