30003598@@@@@@Water dispenser and Big Data@@@@1@5@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:970@LMC@2019-06-14
30003599@@@@@@Background:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:971@LMC@2019-06-14
30003600@@@@@@Drinking water is essential to our health.@@@@1@7@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:972@LMC@2019-06-14
30003601@@@@@@The accessibility of drinking water is very important.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:973@LMC@2019-06-14
30003602@@@@@@Therefore, water dispenser is widely used in our city.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:974@LMC@2019-06-14
30003603@@@@@@Water dispensers are appliances or devices that distribute drinking water in an efficient and highly accessible method.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:975@LMC@2019-06-14
30003604@@@@@@Water dispenser usually contains a filtration system and water tank.@@@@1@10@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:976@LMC@2019-06-14
30003605@@@@@@On the other hand, big data is a concept of collecting huge amount of structural and unstructured data that being generated in our daily life for analytics purpose and aid in decision making.@@@@1@33@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:977@LMC@2019-06-14
30003606@@@@@@(Marr, 2015, p. 9 – 10)@@@@1@6@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:978@LMC@2019-06-14
30003607@@@@@@Problem:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:979@LMC@2019-06-14
30003608@@@@@@People in ntu campus are combining hot water and cold water to obtain warm water using water dispenser.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:980@LMC@2019-06-14
30003609@@@@@@In a survey done on 21 September 2015, 84.4% of ntu students demanded warm water in campus, but the water dispenser provide hot water or cold water only.@@@@1@28@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:981@LMC@2019-06-14
30003610@@@@@@A lot of electricity is used for generating hot and cold water but people simply combine them to become room temperature.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:982@LMC@2019-06-14
30003611@@@@@@Through calculation, energy that used to heat 1 litre of hot water can power a ceiling fan for 2 hours.@@@@1@20@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:983@LMC@2019-06-14
30003612@@@@@@Besides that, each area of campus has different demand of cold, warm and hot water.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:984@LMC@2019-06-14
30003613@@@@@@Weather will also affect the choice of drinking water.@@@@1@9@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:985@LMC@2019-06-14
30003614@@@@@@However, water dispenser generate same amount of water at every time.@@@@1@11@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:986@LMC@2019-06-14
30003615@@@@@@This causes inconvenience and wastage of electrical energy.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:987@LMC@2019-06-14
30003616@@@@@@Solution:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:988@LMC@2019-06-14
30003617@@@@@@The main goal of this proposal is to save electricity and increase the efficiency of water dispenser through big data concept.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:989@LMC@2019-06-14
30003618@@@@@@Water dispenser that provides cold, warm and hot water should be provided in ntu campus.@@@@1@15@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:990@LMC@2019-06-14
30003619@@@@@@Each water dispenser should include temperature sensor and flow rate sensor that collect data of usage of cold, warm, and hot water.@@@@1@22@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:991@LMC@2019-06-14
30003620@@@@@@Then, every water dispenser is connect to a central control system using intranet.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:992@LMC@2019-06-14
30003621@@@@@@Data is collected for analysis.@@@@1@5@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:993@LMC@2019-06-14
30003622@@@@@@Control system will regulate the amount of water of each temperature that prepared by water dispenser in different area of campus.@@@@1@21@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:994@LMC@2019-06-14
30003623@@@@@@This will greatly save energy because only the demanded drinking water is prepared.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:995@LMC@2019-06-14
30003624@@@@@@Benefits:@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:996@LMC@2019-06-14
30003625@@@@@@The cost of providing drinking water in campus will be reduced because the wastage of electricity is reduced.@@@@1@18@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:997@LMC@2019-06-14
30003626@@@@@@Analytics provide an insight of drinking water and aid in decision making.@@@@1@12@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:998@LMC@2019-06-14
30003627@@@@@@For example, water dispenser that located in area that has small demand of drinking water can be moved to area that has larger demand.@@@@1@24@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:999@LMC@2019-06-14
30003628@@@@@@Analytics can also help to improve students’ health.@@@@1@8@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:1000@LMC@2019-06-14
30003629@@@@@@Information of drinking water consumed by each student can be computed, a reminder of drinking more water can be sent to student if they consume too less water.@@@@1@28@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:1001@LMC@2019-06-14
30003630@@@@@@Implementation@@@@1@1@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:1002@LMC@2019-06-14
30003631@@@@@@Three water tanks will be installed in water dispenser to contain cold, warm and hot drinking water.@@@@1@17@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:1003@LMC@2019-06-14
30003632@@@@@@A microcontroller with LAN capability is the main “brain” for the water dispenser.@@@@1@13@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:1004@LMC@2019-06-14
30003633@@@@@@All the water dispenser will be connected to a mini server through the concept of Internet of Things (IoT).@@@@1@19@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:1005@LMC@2019-06-14
30003634@@@@@@Marr (2015) conclude that “the Internet of Things (IoT) is a result of more objects being manufactured with embedded sensors and the ability of those objects to communicate with each other.” (p. 78) all of the water dispenser will send the data to mini server without interference of human being.@@@@1@50@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:1006@LMC@2019-06-14
30003635@@@@@@In the mini server, program algorithms is used to calculate the information and send command back to water dispenser to regulate the amount of water generated.@@@@1@26@ntucle-docid:130; ntucle-sid:1007@LMC@2019-06-14
